Bridget Klecker, 42, of San Francisco, died on Friday after being struck by a car fleeing police in San Francisco .
Police tried to stop the suspects' stolen car around 10pm on Friday just moments after they committed the latest in a series of robberies while armed with handguns .
Klecker was in a crosswalk when the car sped off with police in pursuit and struck a second pedestrian .
Two firearms believed to be thrown from the car were recovered .